6.2.4.3 CONTEXT ATTRIBUTES

Non-Singular Existence

Some features exist only in multiples on a part. An ejection pin is an example of a feature that is always found more than once on a part. If a given form can be identified as an ejection pin, but only one such ejection pin would exist, then the form is not likely an ejection pin.

Models for Concurrent Engineering Design - 15 Jul 1997
